Aug 2017
https://securityintelligence.com/news/insider-threats-account-for-nearly-75-percent-of-security-breach-incidents/
"Not all insider threats are deliberate. In a survey of its attendees, organizers of the annual Black Hat security conference showed that 84 percent of cyberattacks reported had been due to human error, Computer Weekly reported. This could include failing to apply a patch, using easy-to-guess passwords or leaving physical devices in an unsafe area."

https://www.computerweekly.com/news/450425184/Security-professionals-name-top-causes-of-breaches
"The survey revealed 84% of respondents whose company has suffered a cyber attack attribute it, at least in part, to human error."


Opinion Piece:
Nuix "The Human Vulnerability" 
"One of the key findings of my research is that technology is rarely the cause of data
breaches – in the more than 2,500 breaches I have investigated, I can count exactly
zero that were caused by a random, non-human-initiated system failure"

Jordan Schroeder
Every breach report in the media seems to indicate some human factor as a root cause.



